# CI before push (permawrite)

GitHub CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) runs: **rustfmt**, **clippy** (`-D warnings`), **test --release** on Linux/macOS/Windows, and **cargo-audit**.

## Before every `git push` to `main`

1. Run the local mirror (do not skip):
   - Windows: `powershell -File scripts/ci-check.ps1`
   - Linux/macOS: `bash scripts/ci-check.sh`
2. If anything fails, fix it and re-run until green.

`cargo fmt --all` is required; CI uses `cargo fmt --all --check` and **will fail** on unformatted diffs.

## After pushing (agent must do this — user should not paste logs)

1. `gh run list --workflow CI --limit 3`
2. If the latest run failed: `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed`  
   Or: `powershell -File scripts/gh-ci-failed.ps1`
3. Fix failures on `main` in a follow-up commit; do not leave red CI.

## Common failures

| Job | Typical cause |
|-----|----------------|
| rustfmt | Run `cargo fmt --all` and commit |
| clippy | Fix warnings (workspace uses `-D warnings`) |
| test (windows-latest) | Integration tests; build `mfnd` release first |
| cargo-audit | Advisory in dependency tree |

Do not push large Rust changes without running `scripts/ci-check` first.
